    "reasoning": "From the functional equation, setting x=y=z=0 gives 3f(0)=0, so f(0)=0. Hence k = f(0)+1 = 1. We need integers n > 1 such that n divides x^{13} - x for all positive integers x. This condition holds if and only if n is squarefree and for every prime p dividing n, p-1 divides 12. The primes p with p-1 dividing 12 are 2, 3, 5, 7, 13. Thus n is a product of a subset of these primes. There are 2^5 = 32 subsets, including the empty product 1. Excluding n=1 gives 31 such integers n.",
